## System Description
Weather sandbox dynamics: per-tile hydrology on 256x128 terrain. Each tile has surface_water, soil_moisture, groundwater, discharge. Tick pipeline: precipitation→snowmelt→infiltration→evaporation→WSE multi-neighbor flow routing→D8 steepest-descent discharge accumulation. Timestep ~0.03 days (30fps). Grid is 1 tile ≈ 1km. D8 downhill array computed at init with SINK_TOLERANCE=0.002 (creates ~7% sinks). Topo order sorts all tiles descending elevation. Discharge uses 70/30 EMA (old/new). Headwater minimum fixed contribution for elev>0.55.

## Problematic Behavior
TWO ISSUES: (1) NO SMALL LAKES: Despite 663-1263 D8 sinks (7% of land), lake diagnostics show only 2-3 large lakes (>50 tiles) and zero small/medium lakes (5-50 tile range). WSE routing with 0.005 minimum gradient drains most depressions before they fill. Need realistic scattered small lakes in terrain depressions. (2) STATIC RIVERS: Discharge values barely change with weather. Rivers should swell during heavy rainfall and shrink during drought. The 70/30 EMA is too sluggish. Current discharge_max ranges 0.15-1.04 across presets but within a single run, values appear nearly constant. Need visible temporal variation in discharge that responds to precipitation events.

Please tell me what telemetry/metrics you need to diagnose this. Be specific about distributions, time series, budgets, and spatial breakdowns.

